<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Using ZendFramework-0.1.3 and trying the sample code for Service Yahoo:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
&lt;?php
require_once 'Zend/Service/Yahoo.php';
$yahoo = new Zend_Service_Yahoo("YAHOO_APPLICATION_ID");
$results = $yahoo-&gt;webSearch('PHP');
foreach ($results as $result) {
    echo $result-&gt;Title .'<br />';
}
?&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>I get the following error:</p>

<p>Fatal error: Call to a member function setHost() on a non-object in library/Zend/Service/Yahoo.php on line 299</p>

<p>If, in said file, I change that line from,</p>

<p>$this-&gt;_uri-&gt;setHost('api.search.yahoo.com');</p>

<p>To,</p>

<p>$this-&gt;_rest-&gt;setUri('<a href="http://api.search.yahoo.com">http://api.search.yahoo.com</a>');</p>

<p>Then I see successful completion</p>

<p>{quote}
06/07/06 09:19:48: Modified by skelly@idsociety.com</p>

<p>btw, I'm running MAMP on a G4 powerbook, though I get the same error running Linux.</p>

<p>Also, turning on warnings I get the following warning:</p>

<p>Notice: Undefined property: Zend_Service_Yahoo::$_uri in /Applications/MAMP/htdocs/ZendFramework-0.1.3/library/Zend/Service/Yahoo.php on line 299</p>

<p>{quote}</p>

